Package org.checkerframework.framework.ajava

Class DoubleJavaParserVisitor

java.lang.Object
com.github.javaparser.ast.visitor.VoidVisitorAdapter<com.github.javaparser.ast.Node>
org.checkerframework.framework.ajava.DoubleJavaParserVisitor
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.github.javaparser.ast.visitor.VoidVisitor<com.github.javaparser.ast.Node>
Direct Known Subclasses:
AnnotationEqualityVisitor
public abstract class DoubleJavaParserVisitor extends com.github.javaparser.ast.visitor.VoidVisitorAdapter<com.github.javaparser.ast.Node>
A visitor that visits two JavaParser ASTs simultaneously that almost match. When calling a visit method, the secondary argument must be another JavaParser Node that represents an AST identical to the first argument except for the exceptions allowed between an ajava file and its corresponding Java file, see the linked section of the manual.

To use this class, extend it and override defaultAction(Node, Node). This method will be called on every pair of nodes in the two ASTs. This class does not visit annotations, since those may differ between the two ASTs.

See the Checker Framework Manual:
ways in which the two visited ASTs may differ
